    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - High-pressure Oil Pump - Removal</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s26511.2">
        <title>Removal</title>
        <svcproc id="s26511.2.1" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Prerequisites</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, make
                        sure the transmission is in neutral, parking brake is set, and wheels are blocked before doing
                        diagnostic or service procedures on engine or vehicle. See
                        <hotlnk xrefid="safety">"Safety Information</hotlnk>."
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Before removing high-pressure oil system components, the following components must be removed
                        or disconnected first. See the appropriate section for removal procedures:
                    </para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Turbocharger assembly</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Oil filter assembly</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Fuel system</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Intake manifold</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
                <note>
                    <para>If removing only the high-pressure oil pump, it's not necessary to remove the branch tube
                        assembly, rear cover or cylinder heads.
                    </para>
                    <para>If you must remove the branch tube assembly, the rear cover and cylinder heads must also be
                        removed. Refer to Rear Cover and Cylinder Head and Valve Train sections.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
